Definition: perennial plant of Europe and America having racemes of white or purplish flowers and intensely bitter trifoliate leaves
Example: often rooting at water margin and spreading across the surface
Synonyms: buckbean, bogbean, bog_myrtle, marsh_trefoil, Menyanthes_trifoliata, aquatic_plant, genus_Menyanthes, m, perennial, plant, of, Europe, and, America, having, racemes, white, or, purplish, flowers, intensely, bitter, trifoliate, leaves, often, rooting, at, water, margin, spreading, across, the, surface
Category: noun.plant
